{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":7000,"text":"Today, I'm going to take you"},{"time":9000,"text":"around the world in 18 minutes."},{"time":11000,"text":"My base of operations is in the U.S.,"},{"time":14000,"text":"but let's start at the other end of the map,"},{"time":16000,"text":"in Kyoto, Japan,"},{"time":18000,"text":"where I was living with a Japanese family"},{"time":21000,"text":"while I was doing part of my dissertational research"},{"time":23000,"text":"15 years ago."},{"time":26000,"text":"I knew even then that I would encounter"},{"time":28000,"text":"cultural differences and misunderstandings,"},{"time":30000,"text":"but they popped up when I least expected it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33000,"text":"On my first day,"},{"time":35000,"text":"I went to a restaurant,"},{"time":37000,"text":"and I ordered a cup of green tea with sugar."},{"time":39000,"text":"After a pause, the waiter said,"},{"time":41000,"text":"\"One does not put sugar in green tea.\""},{"time":45000,"text":"\"I know,\" I said. \"I'm aware of this custom."},{"time":47000,"text":"But I really like my tea sweet.\""},{"time":50000,"text":"In response, he gave me an even more courteous version"},{"time":53000,"text":"of the same explanation."},{"time":55000,"text":"\"One does not put sugar"},{"time":57000,"text":"in green tea.\""},{"time":60000,"text":"\"I understand,\" I said,"},{"time":62000,"text":"\"that the Japanese do not put sugar in their green tea,"},{"time":64000,"text":"but I'd like to put some sugar"},{"time":66000,"text":"in my green tea.\""},{"time":68000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":70000,"text":"Surprised by my insistence,"},{"time":72000,"text":"the waiter took up the issue with the manager."},{"time":74000,"text":"Pretty soon,"},{"time":76000,"text":"a lengthy discussion ensued,"},{"time":78000,"text":"and finally the manager came over to me and said,"},{"time":81000,"text":"\"I am very sorry. We do not have sugar.\""},{"time":84000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":86000,"text":"Well, since I couldn't have my tea the way I wanted it,"},{"time":89000,"text":"I ordered a cup of coffee,"},{"time":91000,"text":"which the waiter brought over promptly."},{"time":93000,"text":"Resting on the saucer"},{"time":95000,"text":"were two packets of sugar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98000,"text":"My failure to procure myself"},{"time":101000,"text":"a cup of sweet, green tea"},{"time":103000,"text":"was not due to a simple misunderstanding."},{"time":106000,"text":"This was due to a fundamental difference"},{"time":108000,"text":"in our ideas about choice."},{"time":111000,"text":"From my American perspective,"},{"time":113000,"text":"when a paying customer makes a reasonable request"},{"time":115000,"text":"based on her preferences,"},{"time":117000,"text":"she has every right to have that request met."},{"time":120000,"text":"The American way, to quote Burger King,"},{"time":122000,"text":"is to \"have it your way,\""},{"time":124000,"text":"because, as Starbucks says,"},{"time":126000,"text":"\"happiness is in your choices.\""},{"time":128000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":130000,"text":"But from the Japanese perspective,"},{"time":133000,"text":"it's their duty to protect those who don't know any better --"},{"time":136000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":138000,"text":"in this case, the ignorant gaijin --"},{"time":140000,"text":"from making the wrong choice."},{"time":143000,"text":"Let's face it: the way I wanted my tea"},{"time":145000,"text":"was inappropriate according to cultural standards,"},{"time":148000,"text":"and they were doing their best to help me save face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"Americans tend to believe"},{"time":153000,"text":"that they've reached some sort of pinnacle"},{"time":155000,"text":"in the way they practice choice."},{"time":157000,"text":"They think that choice, as seen through the American lens"},{"time":160000,"text":"best fulfills an innate and universal"},{"time":162000,"text":"desire for choice in all humans."},{"time":165000,"text":"Unfortunately,"},{"time":167000,"text":"these beliefs are based on assumptions"},{"time":169000,"text":"that don't always hold true"},{"time":171000,"text":"in many countries, in many cultures."},{"time":174000,"text":"At times they don't even hold true"},{"time":176000,"text":"at America's own borders."},{"time":178000,"text":"I'd like to discuss some of these assumptions"},{"time":180000,"text":"and the problems associated with them."},{"time":183000,"text":"As I do so, I hope you'll start thinking"},{"time":185000,"text":"about some of your own assumptions"},{"time":187000,"text":"and how they were shaped by your backgrounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"First assumption:"},{"time":192000,"text":"if a choice affects you,"},{"time":194000,"text":"then you should be the one to make it."},{"time":196000,"text":"This is the only way to ensure"},{"time":198000,"text":"that your preferences and interests"},{"time":200000,"text":"will be most fully accounted for."},{"time":203000,"text":"It is essential for success."},{"time":206000,"text":"In America, the primary locus of choice"},{"time":209000,"text":"is the individual."},{"time":211000,"text":"People must choose for themselves, sometimes sticking to their guns,"},{"time":214000,"text":"regardless of what other people want or recommend."},{"time":217000,"text":"It's called \"being true to yourself.\""},{"time":220000,"text":"But do all individuals benefit"},{"time":222000,"text":"from taking such an approach to choice?"},{"time":225000,"text":"Mark Lepper and I did a series of studies"},{"time":227000,"text":"in which we sought the answer to this very question."},{"time":230000,"text":"In one study,"},{"time":232000,"text":"which we ran in Japantown, San Francisco,"},{"time":235000,"text":"we brought seven- to nine-year-old Anglo- and Asian-American children"},{"time":238000,"text":"into the laboratory,"},{"time":240000,"text":"and we divided them up into three groups."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242000,"text":"The first group came in,"},{"time":244000,"text":"and they were greeted by Miss Smith,"},{"time":246000,"text":"who showed them six big piles of anagram puzzles."},{"time":249000,"text":"The kids got to choose which pile of anagrams they would like to do,"},{"time":252000,"text":"and they even got to choose which marker"},{"time":254000,"text":"they would write their answers with."},{"time":256000,"text":"When the second group of children came in,"},{"time":258000,"text":"they were brought to the same room, shown the same anagrams,"},{"time":261000,"text":"but this time Miss Smith told them"},{"time":263000,"text":"which anagrams to do"},{"time":265000,"text":"and which markers to write their answers with."},{"time":268000,"text":"Now when the third group came in,"},{"time":271000,"text":"they were told that their anagrams and their markers"},{"time":274000,"text":"had been chosen by their mothers."},{"time":276000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":278000,"text":"In reality,"},{"time":280000,"text":"the kids who were told what to do,"},{"time":282000,"text":"whether by Miss Smith or their mothers,"},{"time":284000,"text":"were actually given the very same activity,"},{"time":286000,"text":"which their counterparts in the first group"},{"time":288000,"text":"had freely chosen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290000,"text":"With this procedure, we were able to ensure"},{"time":292000,"text":"that the kids across the three groups"},{"time":294000,"text":"all did the same activity,"},{"time":296000,"text":"making it easier for us to compare performance."},{"time":299000,"text":"Such small differences in the way we administered the activity"},{"time":302000,"text":"yielded striking differences"},{"time":304000,"text":"in how well they performed."},{"time":306000,"text":"Anglo-Americans,"},{"time":308000,"text":"they did two and a half times more anagrams"},{"time":311000,"text":"when they got to choose them,"},{"time":313000,"text":"as compared to when it was"},{"time":315000,"text":"chosen for them by Miss Smith or their mothers."},{"time":318000,"text":"It didn't matter who did the choosing,"},{"time":321000,"text":"if the task was dictated by another,"},{"time":323000,"text":"their performance suffered."},{"time":325000,"text":"In fact, some of the kids were visibly embarrassed"},{"time":328000,"text":"when they were told that their mothers had been consulted."},{"time":331000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":333000,"text":"One girl named Mary said,"},{"time":335000,"text":"\"You asked my mother?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":338000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":340000,"text":"In contrast,"},{"time":342000,"text":"Asian-American children"},{"time":344000,"text":"performed best when they believed"},{"time":346000,"text":"their mothers had made the choice,"},{"time":349000,"text":"second best when they chose for themselves,"},{"time":352000,"text":"and least well when it had been chosen by Miss Smith."},{"time":355000,"text":"A girl named Natsumi"},{"time":357000,"text":"even approached Miss Smith as she was leaving the room"},{"time":359000,"text":"and tugged on her skirt and asked,"},{"time":361000,"text":"\"Could you please tell my mommy"},{"time":363000,"text":"I did it just like she said?\""},{"time":367000,"text":"The first-generation children were strongly influenced"},{"time":370000,"text":"by their immigrant parents'"},{"time":372000,"text":"approach to choice."},{"time":374000,"text":"For them, choice was not just a way"},{"time":376000,"text":"of defining and asserting"},{"time":378000,"text":"their individuality,"},{"time":380000,"text":"but a way to create community and harmony"},{"time":382000,"text":"by deferring to the choices"},{"time":384000,"text":"of people whom they trusted and respected."},{"time":387000,"text":"If they had a concept of being true to one's self,"},{"time":390000,"text":"then that self, most likely,"},{"time":392000,"text":"[was] composed, not of an individual,"},{"time":394000,"text":"but of a collective."},{"time":396000,"text":"Success was just as much about pleasing key figures"},{"time":399000,"text":"as it was about satisfying"},{"time":401000,"text":"one's own preferences."},{"time":403000,"text":"Or, you could say that"},{"time":405000,"text":"the individual's preferences were shaped"},{"time":407000,"text":"by the preferences of specific others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"The assumption then that we do best"},{"time":413000,"text":"when the individual self chooses"},{"time":415000,"text":"only holds"},{"time":417000,"text":"when that self"},{"time":419000,"text":"is clearly divided from others."},{"time":422000,"text":"When, in contrast,"},{"time":424000,"text":"two or more individuals"},{"time":426000,"text":"see their choices and their outcomes"},{"time":428000,"text":"as intimately connected,"},{"time":430000,"text":"then they may amplify one another's success"},{"time":433000,"text":"by turning choosing"},{"time":435000,"text":"into a collective act."},{"time":437000,"text":"To insist that they choose independently"},{"time":440000,"text":"might actually compromise"},{"time":442000,"text":"both their performance"},{"time":444000,"text":"and their relationships."},{"time":446000,"text":"Yet that is exactly what"},{"time":448000,"text":"the American paradigm demands."},{"time":450000,"text":"It leaves little room for interdependence"},{"time":453000,"text":"or an acknowledgment of individual fallibility."},{"time":456000,"text":"It requires that everyone treat choice"},{"time":459000,"text":"as a private and self-defining act."},{"time":463000,"text":"People that have grown up in such a paradigm"},{"time":465000,"text":"might find it motivating,"},{"time":467000,"text":"but it is a mistake to assume"},{"time":469000,"text":"that everyone thrives under the pressure"},{"time":471000,"text":"of choosing alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474000,"text":"The second assumption which informs the American view of choice"},{"time":477000,"text":"goes something like this."},{"time":479000,"text":"The more choices you have,"},{"time":481000,"text":"the more likely you are"},{"time":483000,"text":"to make the best choice."},{"time":485000,"text":"So bring it on, Walmart, with 100,000 different products,"},{"time":488000,"text":"and Amazon, with 27 million books"},{"time":491000,"text":"and Match.com with -- what is it? --"},{"time":493000,"text":"15 million date possibilities now."},{"time":497000,"text":"You will surely find the perfect match."},{"time":500000,"text":"Let's test this assumption"},{"time":502000,"text":"by heading over to Eastern Europe."},{"time":504000,"text":"Here, I interviewed people"},{"time":506000,"text":"who were residents of formerly communist countries,"},{"time":509000,"text":"who had all faced the challenge"},{"time":511000,"text":"of transitioning to a more"},{"time":513000,"text":"democratic and capitalistic society."},{"time":516000,"text":"One of the most interesting revelations"},{"time":518000,"text":"came not from an answer to a question,"},{"time":520000,"text":"but from a simple gesture of hospitality."},{"time":523000,"text":"When the participants arrived for their interview,"},{"time":526000,"text":"I offered them a set of drinks:"},{"time":528000,"text":"Coke, Diet Coke, Sprite --"},{"time":530000,"text":"seven, to be exact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"During the very first session,"},{"time":534000,"text":"which was run in Russia,"},{"time":536000,"text":"one of the participants made a comment"},{"time":538000,"text":"that really caught me off guard."},{"time":541000,"text":"\"Oh, but it doesn't matter."},{"time":543000,"text":"It's all just soda. That's just one choice.\""},{"time":546000,"text":"(Murmuring)"},{"time":548000,"text":"I was so struck by this comment that from then on,"},{"time":550000,"text":"I started to offer all the participants"},{"time":552000,"text":"those seven sodas,"},{"time":554000,"text":"and I asked them, \"How many choices are these?\""},{"time":557000,"text":"Again and again,"},{"time":559000,"text":"they perceived these seven different sodas,"},{"time":562000,"text":"not as seven choices, but as one choice:"},{"time":565000,"text":"soda or no soda."},{"time":567000,"text":"When I put out juice and water"},{"time":569000,"text":"in addition to these seven sodas,"},{"time":571000,"text":"now they perceived it as only three choices --"},{"time":573000,"text":"juice, water and soda."},{"time":576000,"text":"Compare this to the die-hard devotion of many Americans,"},{"time":579000,"text":"not just to a particular flavor of soda,"},{"time":582000,"text":"but to a particular brand."},{"time":584000,"text":"You know, research shows repeatedly"},{"time":587000,"text":"that we can't actually tell the difference"},{"time":589000,"text":"between Coke and Pepsi."},{"time":591000,"text":"Of course, you and I know"},{"time":593000,"text":"that Coke is the better choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"For modern Americans who are exposed"},{"time":603000,"text":"to more options and more ads associated with options"},{"time":606000,"text":"than anyone else in the world,"},{"time":608000,"text":"choice is just as much about who they are"},{"time":610000,"text":"as it is about what the product is."},{"time":613000,"text":"Combine this with the assumption that more choices are always better,"},{"time":616000,"text":"and you have a group of people for whom every little difference matters"},{"time":619000,"text":"and so every choice matters."},{"time":621000,"text":"But for Eastern Europeans,"},{"time":624000,"text":"the sudden availability of all these"},{"time":626000,"text":"consumer products on the marketplace was a deluge."},{"time":629000,"text":"They were flooded with choice"},{"time":631000,"text":"before they could protest that they didn't know how to swim."},{"time":635000,"text":"When asked, \"What words and images"},{"time":637000,"text":"do you associate with choice?\""},{"time":639000,"text":"Grzegorz from Warsaw said,"},{"time":642000,"text":"\"Ah, for me it is fear."},{"time":644000,"text":"There are some dilemmas you see."},{"time":646000,"text":"I am used to no choice.\""},{"time":648000,"text":"Bohdan from Kiev said,"},{"time":650000,"text":"in response to how he felt about"},{"time":652000,"text":"the new consumer marketplace,"},{"time":654000,"text":"\"It is too much."},{"time":656000,"text":"We do not need everything that is there.\""},{"time":658000,"text":"A sociologist from"},{"time":660000,"text":"the Warsaw Survey Agency explained,"},{"time":663000,"text":"\"The older generation jumped from nothing"},{"time":666000,"text":"to choice all around them."},{"time":668000,"text":"They were never given a chance to learn"},{"time":670000,"text":"how to react.\""},{"time":672000,"text":"And Tomasz, a young Polish man said,"},{"time":675000,"text":"\"I don't need twenty kinds of chewing gum."},{"time":678000,"text":"I don't mean to say that I want no choice,"},{"time":681000,"text":"but many of these choices are quite artificial.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"In reality, many choices are between things"},{"time":688000,"text":"that are not that much different."},{"time":692000,"text":"The value of choice"},{"time":694000,"text":"depends on our ability"},{"time":696000,"text":"to perceive differences"},{"time":698000,"text":"between the options."},{"time":700000,"text":"Americans train their whole lives"},{"time":702000,"text":"to play \"spot the difference.\""},{"time":705000,"text":"They practice this from such an early age"},{"time":707000,"text":"that they've come to believe that everyone"},{"time":709000,"text":"must be born with this ability."},{"time":711000,"text":"In fact, though all humans share"},{"time":713000,"text":"a basic need and desire for choice,"},{"time":716000,"text":"we don't all see choice in the same places"},{"time":719000,"text":"or to the same extent."},{"time":721000,"text":"When someone can't see how one choice"},{"time":723000,"text":"is unlike another,"},{"time":725000,"text":"or when there are too many choices to compare and contrast,"},{"time":728000,"text":"the process of choosing can be"},{"time":730000,"text":"confusing and frustrating."},{"time":733000,"text":"Instead of making better choices,"},{"time":735000,"text":"we become overwhelmed by choice,"},{"time":737000,"text":"sometimes even afraid of it."},{"time":740000,"text":"Choice no longer offers opportunities,"},{"time":742000,"text":"but imposes constraints."},{"time":744000,"text":"It's not a marker of liberation,"},{"time":746000,"text":"but of suffocation"},{"time":748000,"text":"by meaningless minutiae."},{"time":750000,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":752000,"text":"choice can develop into the very opposite"},{"time":754000,"text":"of everything it represents"},{"time":756000,"text":"in America"},{"time":758000,"text":"when it is thrust upon those"},{"time":760000,"text":"who are insufficiently prepared for it."},{"time":763000,"text":"But it is not only other people"},{"time":765000,"text":"in other places"},{"time":767000,"text":"that are feeling the pressure"},{"time":769000,"text":"of ever-increasing choice."},{"time":771000,"text":"Americans themselves are discovering"},{"time":773000,"text":"that unlimited choice"},{"time":775000,"text":"seems more attractive in theory"},{"time":777000,"text":"than in practice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779000,"text":"We all have physical, mental"},{"time":782000,"text":"and emotional (Laughter) limitations"},{"time":784000,"text":"that make it impossible for us"},{"time":786000,"text":"to process every single choice we encounter,"},{"time":789000,"text":"even in the grocery store,"},{"time":791000,"text":"let alone over the course of our entire lives."},{"time":794000,"text":"A number of my studies have shown"},{"time":797000,"text":"that when you give people 10 or more options"},{"time":799000,"text":"when they're making a choice, they make poorer decisions,"},{"time":802000,"text":"whether it be health care, investment,"},{"time":804000,"text":"other critical areas."},{"time":806000,"text":"Yet still, many of us believe"},{"time":808000,"text":"that we should make all our own choices"},{"time":811000,"text":"and seek out even more of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814000,"text":"This brings me to the third,"},{"time":817000,"text":"and perhaps most problematic, assumption:"},{"time":820000,"text":"\"You must never"},{"time":822000,"text":"say no to choice.\""},{"time":825000,"text":"To examine this, let's go back to the U.S."},{"time":827000,"text":"and then hop across the pond to France."},{"time":830000,"text":"Right outside Chicago,"},{"time":833000,"text":"a young couple, Susan and Daniel Mitchell,"},{"time":835000,"text":"were about to have their first baby."},{"time":838000,"text":"They'd already picked out a name for her,"},{"time":840000,"text":"Barbara, after her grandmother."},{"time":843000,"text":"One night, when Susan was seven months pregnant,"},{"time":846000,"text":"she started to experience contractions"},{"time":848000,"text":"and was rushed to the emergency room."},{"time":851000,"text":"The baby was delivered through a C-section,"},{"time":854000,"text":"but Barbara suffered cerebral anoxia,"},{"time":856000,"text":"a loss of oxygen to the brain."},{"time":859000,"text":"Unable to breathe on her own,"},{"time":861000,"text":"she was put on a ventilator."},{"time":863000,"text":"Two days later,"},{"time":865000,"text":"the doctors gave the Mitchells"},{"time":867000,"text":"a choice:"},{"time":869000,"text":"They could either remove Barbara"},{"time":871000,"text":"off the life support,"},{"time":873000,"text":"in which case she would die within a matter of hours,"},{"time":876000,"text":"or they could keep her on life support,"},{"time":879000,"text":"in which case she might still die"},{"time":881000,"text":"within a matter of days."},{"time":883000,"text":"If she survived, she would remain"},{"time":885000,"text":"in a permanent vegetative state,"},{"time":888000,"text":"never able to walk, talk"},{"time":891000,"text":"or interact with others."},{"time":894000,"text":"What do they do?"},{"time":896000,"text":"What do any parent do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":902000,"text":"In a study I conducted"},{"time":904000,"text":"with Simona Botti and Kristina Orfali,"},{"time":906000,"text":"American and French parents"},{"time":908000,"text":"were interviewed."},{"time":910000,"text":"They had all suffered"},{"time":912000,"text":"the same tragedy."},{"time":914000,"text":"In all cases, the life support was removed,"},{"time":917000,"text":"and the infants had died."},{"time":919000,"text":"But there was a big difference."},{"time":921000,"text":"In France, the doctors decided whether and when"},{"time":924000,"text":"the life support would be removed,"},{"time":927000,"text":"while in the United States,"},{"time":929000,"text":"the final decision rested with the parents."},{"time":933000,"text":"We wondered:"},{"time":935000,"text":"does this have an effect on how the parents"},{"time":937000,"text":"cope with the loss of their loved one?"},{"time":940000,"text":"We found that it did."},{"time":943000,"text":"Even up to a year later,"},{"time":945000,"text":"American parents"},{"time":947000,"text":"were more likely to express negative emotions,"},{"time":949000,"text":"as compared to their French counterparts."},{"time":952000,"text":"French parents were more likely to say things like,"},{"time":955000,"text":"\"Noah was here for so little time,"},{"time":958000,"text":"but he taught us so much."},{"time":960000,"text":"He gave us a new perspective on life.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":964000,"text":"American parents were more likely to say things like,"},{"time":967000,"text":"\"What if? What if?\""},{"time":970000,"text":"Another parent complained,"},{"time":972000,"text":"\"I feel as if they purposefully tortured me."},{"time":975000,"text":"How did they get me to do that?\""},{"time":978000,"text":"And another parent said,"},{"time":980000,"text":"\"I feel as if I've played a role"},{"time":982000,"text":"in an execution.\""},{"time":985000,"text":"But when the American parents were asked"},{"time":987000,"text":"if they would rather have had"},{"time":989000,"text":"the doctors make the decision,"},{"time":992000,"text":"they all said, \"No.\""},{"time":994000,"text":"They could not imagine"},{"time":996000,"text":"turning that choice over to another,"},{"time":998000,"text":"even though having made that choice"},{"time":1001000,"text":"made them feel trapped,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"guilty, angry."},{"time":1005000,"text":"In a number of cases"},{"time":1007000,"text":"they were even clinically depressed."},{"time":1010000,"text":"These parents could not contemplate"},{"time":1012000,"text":"giving up the choice,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"because to do so would have gone contrary"},{"time":1016000,"text":"to everything they had been taught"},{"time":1019000,"text":"and everything they had come to believe"},{"time":1021000,"text":"about the power"},{"time":1023000,"text":"and purpose of choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026000,"text":"In her essay, \"The White Album,\""},{"time":1029000,"text":"Joan Didion writes,"},{"time":1032000,"text":"\"We tell ourselves stories"},{"time":1034000,"text":"in order to live."},{"time":1036000,"text":"We interpret what we see,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"select the most workable"},{"time":1040000,"text":"of the multiple choices."},{"time":1042000,"text":"We live entirely by the imposition"},{"time":1044000,"text":"of a narrative line"},{"time":1046000,"text":"upon disparate images,"},{"time":1048000,"text":"by the idea with which we have learned to freeze"},{"time":1051000,"text":"the shifting phantasmagoria,"},{"time":1053000,"text":"which is our actual experience.\""},{"time":1058000,"text":"The story Americans tell,"},{"time":1060000,"text":"the story upon which"},{"time":1062000,"text":"the American dream depends,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"is the story of limitless choice."},{"time":1067000,"text":"This narrative"},{"time":1069000,"text":"promises so much:"},{"time":1071000,"text":"freedom, happiness,"},{"time":1073000,"text":"success."},{"time":1075000,"text":"It lays the world at your feet and says,"},{"time":1078000,"text":"\"You can have anything, everything.\""},{"time":1082000,"text":"It's a great story,"},{"time":1084000,"text":"and it's understandable why they would be reluctant"},{"time":1086000,"text":"to revise it."},{"time":1089000,"text":"But when you take a close look,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"you start to see the holes,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"and you start to see that the story"},{"time":1095000,"text":"can be told in many other ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1098000,"text":"Americans have so often tried to"},{"time":1100000,"text":"disseminate their ideas of choice,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"believing that they will be, or ought to be,"},{"time":1106000,"text":"welcomed with open hearts and minds."},{"time":1109000,"text":"But the history books and the daily news tell us"},{"time":1112000,"text":"it doesn't always work out that way."},{"time":1115000,"text":"The phantasmagoria,"},{"time":1117000,"text":"the actual experience that we try to understand"},{"time":1119000,"text":"and organize through narrative,"},{"time":1122000,"text":"varies from place to place."},{"time":1125000,"text":"No single narrative serves the needs"},{"time":1127000,"text":"of everyone everywhere."},{"time":1131000,"text":"Moreover, Americans themselves"},{"time":1134000,"text":"could benefit from incorporating"},{"time":1137000,"text":"new perspectives into their own narrative,"},{"time":1140000,"text":"which has been driving their choices"},{"time":1142000,"text":"for so long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1145000,"text":"Robert Frost once said that,"},{"time":1148000,"text":"\"It is poetry that is lost in translation.\""},{"time":1152000,"text":"This suggests that"},{"time":1154000,"text":"whatever is beautiful and moving,"},{"time":1156000,"text":"whatever gives us a new way to see,"},{"time":1159000,"text":"cannot be communicated to those"},{"time":1161000,"text":"who speak a different language."},{"time":1164000,"text":"But Joseph Brodsky said that,"},{"time":1166000,"text":"\"It is poetry"},{"time":1168000,"text":"that is gained in translation,\""},{"time":1170000,"text":"suggesting that translation"},{"time":1172000,"text":"can be a creative,"},{"time":1174000,"text":"transformative act."},{"time":1177000,"text":"When it comes to choice,"},{"time":1179000,"text":"we have far more to gain than to lose"},{"time":1182000,"text":"by engaging in the many"},{"time":1185000,"text":"translations of the narratives."},{"time":1188000,"text":"Instead of replacing"},{"time":1190000,"text":"one story with another,"},{"time":1192000,"text":"we can learn from and revel in"},{"time":1194000,"text":"the many versions that exist"},{"time":1197000,"text":"and the many that have yet to be written."},{"time":1200000,"text":"No matter where we're from"},{"time":1203000,"text":"and what your narrative is,"},{"time":1205000,"text":"we all have a responsibility"},{"time":1207000,"text":"to open ourselves up to a wider array"},{"time":1209000,"text":"of what choice can do,"},{"time":1212000,"text":"and what it can represent."},{"time":1215000,"text":"And this does not lead to"},{"time":1217000,"text":"a paralyzing moral relativism."},{"time":1220000,"text":"Rather, it teaches us when"},{"time":1222000,"text":"and how to act."},{"time":1224000,"text":"It brings us that much closer"},{"time":1226000,"text":"to realizing the full potential of choice,"},{"time":1229000,"text":"to inspiring the hope"},{"time":1231000,"text":"and achieving the freedom"},{"time":1233000,"text":"that choice promises"},{"time":1235000,"text":"but doesn't always deliver."},{"time":1237000,"text":"If we learn to speak to one another,"},{"time":1240000,"text":"albeit through translation,"},{"time":1243000,"text":"then we can begin to see choice"},{"time":1245000,"text":"in all its strangeness,"},{"time":1247000,"text":"complexity"},{"time":1250000,"text":"and compelling beauty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1252000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1254000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1265000,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Thank you."},{"time":1268000,"text":"Sheena, there is a detail about your biography"},{"time":1271000,"text":"that we have not written in the program book."},{"time":1273000,"text":"But by now it's evident to everyone in this room. You're blind."},{"time":1276000,"text":"And I guess one of the questions on everybody's mind is:"},{"time":1279000,"text":"How does that influence your study of choosing"},{"time":1282000,"text":"because that's an activity"},{"time":1284000,"text":"that for most people is associated with visual inputs"},{"time":1287000,"text":"like aesthetics and color and so on?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1291000,"text":"Sheena Iyengar: Well, it's funny that you should ask that"},{"time":1293000,"text":"because one of the things that's interesting about being blind"},{"time":1296000,"text":"is you actually get a different vantage point"},{"time":1298000,"text":"when you observe the way"},{"time":1300000,"text":"sighted people make choices."},{"time":1302000,"text":"And as you just mentioned, there's lots of choices out there"},{"time":1304000,"text":"that are very visual these days."},{"time":1306000,"text":"Yeah, I -- as you would expect --"},{"time":1308000,"text":"get pretty frustrated by choices"},{"time":1310000,"text":"like what nail polish to put on"},{"time":1312000,"text":"because I have to rely on what other people suggest."},{"time":1314000,"text":"And I can't decide."},{"time":1316000,"text":"And so one time I was in a beauty salon,"},{"time":1318000,"text":"and I was trying to decide between two very light shades of pink."},{"time":1321000,"text":"And one was called \"Ballet Slippers.\""},{"time":1323000,"text":"And the other one was called \"Adorable.\""},{"time":1326000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1328000,"text":"And so I asked these two ladies,"},{"time":1330000,"text":"and the one lady told me, \"Well, you should definitely wear 'Ballet Slippers.'\""},{"time":1332000,"text":"\"Well, what does it look like?\""},{"time":1334000,"text":"\"Well, it's a very elegant shade of pink.\""},{"time":1336000,"text":"\"Okay, great.\""},{"time":1338000,"text":"The other lady tells me to wear \"Adorable.\""},{"time":1340000,"text":"\"What does it look like?\""},{"time":1342000,"text":"\"It's a glamorous shade of pink.\""},{"time":1346000,"text":"And so I asked them, \"Well, how do I tell them apart?"},{"time":1348000,"text":"What's different about them?\""},{"time":1350000,"text":"And they said, \"Well, one is elegant, the other one's glamorous.\""},{"time":1352000,"text":"Okay, we got that."},{"time":1354000,"text":"And the only thing they had consensus on:"},{"time":1356000,"text":"well, if I could see them, I would"},{"time":1358000,"text":"clearly be able to tell them apart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1360000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1362000,"text":"And what I wondered was whether they were being affected"},{"time":1365000,"text":"by the name or the content of the color,"},{"time":1367000,"text":"so I decided to do a little experiment."},{"time":1370000,"text":"So I brought these two bottles of nail polish into the laboratory,"},{"time":1373000,"text":"and I stripped the labels off."},{"time":1375000,"text":"And I brought women into the laboratory,"},{"time":1377000,"text":"and I asked them, \"Which one would you pick?\""},{"time":1379000,"text":"50 percent of the women accused me of playing a trick,"},{"time":1382000,"text":"of putting the same color nail polish"},{"time":1384000,"text":"in both those bottles."},{"time":1386000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1388000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1392000,"text":"At which point you start to wonder who the trick's really played on."},{"time":1395000,"text":"Now, of the women that could tell them apart,"},{"time":1398000,"text":"when the labels were off, they picked \"Adorable,\""},{"time":1401000,"text":"and when the labels were on,"},{"time":1403000,"text":"they picked \"Ballet Slippers.\""},{"time":1406000,"text":"So as far as I can tell,"},{"time":1408000,"text":"a rose by any other name"},{"time":1410000,"text":"probably does look different"},{"time":1412000,"text":"and maybe even smells different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1415000,"text":"BG: Thank you. Sheena Iyengar. Thank you Sheena."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1418000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}